data.description: Fantastic opportunity to live in this beautiful home situated in a highly desired Swim/Tennis community ,McKendree Park, popular Lake Community & Collins Hill School District!As you step into the 2-story foyer, the main level unfolds with a thoughtfully designed layout. To your left, a sophisticated office space awaits, providing a quiet retreat for productivity or study.Continue into the right of the home, where the living room welcomes you with its warm ambiance. it's an inviting space for relaxation and conversation. The adjacent dining room, bathed in natural light, sets the scene for memorable meals and gatherings.  The open-concept kitchen boasts functional amenities and ample counter spaces.The vaulted family room with fire place and built-in cabinets creates an expansive and airy atmosphere. This space is perfect for unwinding with loved ones, watching movies, or simply enjoying the warmth of the fireplace on chilly evenings.Throughout the main level, large windows which were all replaced in 2021 showcase views of the surrounding landscape, bringing the outdoors in and creating a seamless connection to nature. Ascend the staircase to the second floor, the master bedroom is a retreat within itself, offering a spacious and serene escape.Connected to the master bedroom, the ensuite master bathroom is a sanctuary of luxury. Equipped with dual vanities , a rejuvenating bathtub, and a separate shower, it provides a private oasis for unwinding after a long day. Down the hallway, discover three secondary rooms that share a well-appointed full bathroom. Each of these rooms is thoughtfully designed to accommodate various needs, whether they serve as bedrooms, guest rooms, gym or home offices. The neutral tones and large windows continue on this floor, creating a cohesive and comfortable ambiance throughout.Venture down to the partially finished basement, a versatile space brimming with potential and awaiting your creative touch. whether you dream of a spacious recreation room, a home gym, a workshop, or a cozy home theater, the possibilities are unlimited.Home has been well maintained and improved: new exterior paint 2021,new windows 2021,new deck and pergola 2021,new hardwood floor 2021,new stairs and 2nd floor carpet 2023. HOA no rental restriction! Investors welcome!  Zoned to award-winning schools and located very close to lots of shopping, restaurants, theatres, Gas South Arena, and Cool Ray Field. Minutes to I-85, Hwy. 316 and Sugarloaf Mills. Just minutes to all of the fun activities, shopping and restaurants in downtown Lawrenceville Square, I-85, Hwy 316, Mall of Georgia and MORE!
